item.value: /** * When {@link #FLAG_DIM_BEHIND} is set, this is the amount of dimming * to apply. Range is from 1.0 for completely opaque to 0.0 for no * dim.

An app can use this method to check if it is currently allowed to draw on top of other * apps. In order to be allowed to do so, an app must first declare the * {@link android.Manifest.permission#SYSTEM_ALERT_WINDOW} permission in its manifest. If it * is currently disallowed, it can prompt the user to grant it this capability through a * management UI by sending an Intent with action * {@link android.provider.Settings#ACTION_MANAGE_OVERLAY_PERMISSION}. * * @param context A context * @return true if the calling app can draw on top of other apps, false otherwise.
